{
  "stem": "20021.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 13.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But in particular what I remember during Shabbos, that after the meal on Saturday, my father would take me on his knee and I would tell him what I learned from the Talmud and from the Tanakh, which is the Prophets and the Torah, this particular week.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I was looking forwards to it very much.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "First of all, it was an opportunity to show off before him.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And this was sweet.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I still remember that.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then my mother would buy sweets, chocolates, you know, the best, which during the week we were not supposed to eat, for various reasons, you know, the teeth would go wrong and all that.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But after this sort of examination, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] there will be all those sweets, [LAUGHS] a sort of a reward for that and all that.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And-- but primarily it wasn't the sweets.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was really an opportunity to show off before my father, which meant an awful lot to me.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And he was trying to be critical and ask me questions, sort of difficult questions.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I had to withstand this test, so it was challenging also.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It wasn't only-- and every once in a while, if I didn't live up to the expectations, he would show me that I didn't live up to the expectations.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So having passed it was-- was very fulfilling.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, for Shabbos--",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Always.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Primarily the family.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "However, there was the custom in the synagogue that if a man arrived from another town or for whatever reason, the shamas, which was like a sexton, you know, he would go around and ask people to take him on for Sabbath for a Sabbath meal.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And because there was more than one, most of the time my father would end up taking somebody home.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
